                <note rend="inline" type="source">881.7961/26: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé at Tangier</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Childs</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-12-03T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >December 3, 1942—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>248. Your 703, November 26. You may inform General Orgaz that the War Department
                    has instructed the appropriate American military authorities not to permit
                    American planes to fly over Spanish territory in North Africa.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
